data.text: @thetopexception Professor I know thought everyone was just being a baby about the shot and then she got it she said it felt like somebody cracked her arm with a baseball bat.

@thetopexception I did mine @ Medgar Evers last Monday and I’ve been feeling sick since then.  Chills, tremors, fever, trouble breathing... arm soreness left after 24h though. Side effects are most likely bc I already had Covid - hopefully you’ll be fine.

@thetopexception With first shot arm got very sore about 8-10 hrs. later. Kept me up all night. Gradually got better by third day. With second shot I moved arm more after and iced it and took Tylenol at bedtime. Much less sore. Good luck!
@thetopexception my arm hurt for almost a full 24 hours if that helps you plan your workouts!!
